The paper presents a method for representing database columns using distributed representations, which is relevant to the field of database management (cs.DB). The use of natural language processing techniques to generate appropriate names for unnamed columns suggests a connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL). The training of a model to generate appropriate names for columns involves machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Finally, the use of schema information from open source applications suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
